rComments: Erin Vogel is truly an asset to the anthro dept. I fell in love with field primatology because of this class. She is a ridiculously difficult grader, but then again this class isn't meant for students who aren't serious. We got to actually monitor the activity budget of a focal primate at the SF zoo. Best part of the class!
Erin is a great teacher who really knows her stuff.  She made statistics interesting, and the final was fun.

She continues to disappoint me by holding grudges and being petty. She really needs to come to terms with being a teacher NOT a peer. -Advice- Even if you know the information by heart, act amazed and "try real hard" because effort apparently overshadows ability in Vogeland.  She's no Nate, but with a little maturity she could be.
